  "prompt": "What are some major problems faced by girls during their periods?",
  "response": "Girls and women often face several challenges during menstruation:\n\nPhysical Problems:\n1. Menstrual cramps and abdominal pain\n2. Headaches\n3. Lower back pain\n4. Fatigue and weakness\n5. Bloating\n6. Nausea\n7. Hormonal mood swings\n8. Irregular flow and heavy bleeding\n\nPsychological Problems:\n1. Anxiety and stress\n2. Depression\n3. Low self-esteem\n4. Body image issues\n5. Discomfort and embarrassment\n\nSocial and Practical Challenges:\n1. Limited access to sanitary products\n2. Lack of proper menstrual hygiene facilities\n3. Stigma and cultural taboos\n4. School/work absenteeism\n5. Inadequate reproductive health education\n6. Potential discrimination\n\nHealth-related Issues:\n1. Potential anemia due to heavy bleeding\n2. Hormonal imbalances\n3. Reproductive health complications\n4. Risk of infections if proper hygiene is not maintained\n\nPersonal Challenges:\n1. Disruption of daily activities\n2. Physical discomfort during sports/exercise\n3. Sleep disturbances\n4. Dietary restrictions in some cultures\n\nThese challenges vary across different regions, cultures, and individual experiences.",
